00:00:08.308 --> 00:00:10.845 position:7% line:83% align:start
[narrator] The following tale
begins on June 5th

00:00:10.879 --> 00:00:13.748 position:24% line:89% align:start
in the year 1972.

00:00:13.781 --> 00:00:17.317 position:7% line:83% align:start
It was a dark and humid night
in America's Deep South

00:00:17.351 --> 00:00:19.654 position:19% line:83% align:start
when the first cry of
a newborn child rang

00:00:19.687 --> 00:00:22.089 position:21% line:83% align:start
through the halls of
a maternity hospital.

00:00:23.691 --> 00:00:25.325 position:38% line:83% align:start
However,
before that baby had

00:00:25.359 --> 00:00:27.094 position:24% line:83% align:start
the chance to see
the light of day,

00:00:27.127 --> 00:00:29.029 position:19% line:83% align:start
his life expired while
still curled

00:00:29.062 --> 00:00:31.365 position:13% line:89% align:start
in the arms of his mother.

00:00:31.398 --> 00:00:33.267 position:21% line:83% align:start
To the young mother
who had never once

00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:35.135 position:19% line:83% align:start
felt that she had been
living a life

00:00:35.168 --> 00:00:38.138 position:5% line:83% align:start
that consisted of any happiness
or sense of purpose,

00:00:38.171 --> 00:00:41.208 position:5% line:83% align:start
her newborn son was going to be
a symbol of the hope

00:00:41.241 --> 00:00:43.845 position:21% line:83% align:start
that she would have
a better future.

00:00:43.878 --> 00:00:45.747 position:21% line:83% align:start
With her first child
lost to her,

00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:49.082 position:10% line:83% align:start
that potential happiness she
longed for was lost as well,

00:00:49.116 --> 00:00:51.485 position:24% line:83% align:start
and she was unable
to accept his death.

00:00:52.486 --> 00:00:54.388 position:7% line:83% align:start
Before the doctors and nurses
could learn

00:00:54.421 --> 00:00:56.558 position:30% line:83% align:start
of the baby's
unfortunate passing,

00:00:56.591 --> 00:00:58.458 position:27% line:83% align:start
the young mother
slipped out of her bed

00:00:58.492 --> 00:01:00.460 position:16% line:83% align:start
as if she were a phantom
in the night.

00:01:01.328 --> 00:01:03.363 position:27% line:83% align:start
She made her way
into another room

00:01:03.397 --> 00:01:05.232 position:24% line:83% align:start
where she replaced
her deceased child

00:01:05.265 --> 00:01:07.301 position:19% line:83% align:start
with one who was born
the same day

00:01:07.334 --> 00:01:08.503 position:19% line:89% align:start
and made him her own.

00:01:09.737 --> 00:01:11.471 position:7% line:89% align:start
This other baby which she took

00:01:11.506 --> 00:01:13.608 position:27% line:83% align:start
was one of a set
of fraternal twins.

00:01:14.341 --> 00:01:15.843 position:7% line:89% align:start
To this day, the incident was

00:01:15.877 --> 00:01:17.745 position:27% line:83% align:start
never questioned
or investigated,

00:01:17.779 --> 00:01:21.415 position:13% line:83% align:start
and not even a single soul
suspected a thing.

00:01:21.448 --> 00:01:23.216 position:30% line:89% align:start
[somber music]

00:01:24.819 --> 00:01:27.187 position:19% line:83% align:start
[young Father Pucchi]
Mama, whose grave is this?

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:29.222 position:30% line:83% align:start
They were born
the same day as me.

00:01:29.958 --> 00:01:31.291 position:30% line:89% align:start
Died then too.

00:01:32.225 --> 00:01:33.460 position:24% line:83% align:start
-[mother] Enrico.
-Huh?

00:01:34.596 --> 00:01:36.731 position:38% line:83% align:start
[mother]
The truth of the matter is,

00:01:36.764 --> 00:01:38.533 position:13% line:89% align:start
you had a younger brother.

00:01:38.566 --> 00:01:40.535 position:30% line:83% align:start
The two of you
were fraternal twins.

00:01:40.568 --> 00:01:41.703 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:01:41.736 --> 00:01:43.103 position:10% line:83% align:start
[mother] But he passed away
at the hospital

00:01:43.136 --> 00:01:44.505 position:16% line:89% align:start
right after he was born.

00:01:46.674 --> 00:01:47.441 position:30% line:89% align:start
Pray for him.

00:01:48.943 --> 00:01:50.612 position:33% line:89% align:start
Afterwards,

00:01:50.645 --> 00:01:53.681 position:19% line:83% align:start
we decided to give him
the name Domenic.

00:01:53.715 --> 00:01:56.249 position:21% line:89% align:start
[church bell tolls]

00:01:59.286 --> 00:02:01.723 position:19% line:83% align:start
[young Father Pucchi]
Lord, answer my plea.

00:02:01.756 --> 00:02:03.791 position:13% line:83% align:start
My brother and I were born
on the same day,

00:02:03.825 --> 00:02:06.259 position:16% line:89% align:start
but I lived and he died.

00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:08.195 position:10% line:77% align:start
choose to take my brother's
life and not mine?
For what reason did fate

00:02:08.228 --> 00:02:10.330 position:10% line:83% align:start
choose to take my brother's
life and not mine?

00:02:11.532 --> 00:02:15.202 position:10% line:83% align:start
And why do humans experience
happiness and misfortune?

00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:18.673 position:16% line:89% align:start
What is true happiness?

00:02:18.706 --> 00:02:22.076 position:16% line:83% align:start
[narrator] At this time,
Enrico was aged 15.

00:02:22.110 --> 00:02:23.945 position:19% line:83% align:start
His great-grandmother
on his father's side

00:02:23.978 --> 00:02:25.580 position:13% line:89% align:start
was an Italian immigrant.

00:02:26.446 --> 00:02:28.215 position:21% line:83% align:start
He is descended from
a prestigious

00:02:28.248 --> 00:02:29.984 position:19% line:83% align:start
and influential family
in Venice,

00:02:30.018 --> 00:02:31.418 position:27% line:83% align:start
in which one of
his family members

00:02:31.451 --> 00:02:32.754 position:13% line:89% align:start
became a famous clergyman

00:02:32.787 --> 00:02:34.689 position:16% line:89% align:start
during the 18th century.

00:02:34.722 --> 00:02:38.526 position:7% line:83% align:start
So, when young Enrico declared
he wanted to attend a seminary,

00:02:38.559 --> 00:02:41.328 position:16% line:83% align:start
there wasn't one member
of his family who objected.

00:02:41.361 --> 00:02:42.964 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[thuds]
-[young Father Pucchi grunts]

00:02:42.997 --> 00:02:44.032 position:35% line:89% align:start
[rattling]

00:02:44.065 --> 00:02:44.899 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:02:45.700 --> 00:02:46.968 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:02:47.001 --> 00:02:49.336 position:19% line:83% align:start
Hey, is someone here?
Who's there?

00:02:51.338 --> 00:02:53.141 position:38% line:83% align:start
Tell me,
what are you doing in here?

00:02:53.173 --> 00:02:54.241 position:41% line:89% align:start
[zaps]

00:02:54.274 --> 00:02:55.308 position:38% line:83% align:start
[grunts]
Hold it!

00:02:55.342 --> 00:02:56.577 position:5% line:89% align:start
[young Dio] Is this book yours?

00:02:56.611 --> 00:02:58.378 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:02:58.412 --> 00:03:01.983 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's a famous biography by a
clergyman who commits adultery

00:03:02.016 --> 00:03:04.418 position:33% line:83% align:start
and runs off
to become a painter.

00:03:04.451 --> 00:03:06.087 position:16% line:89% align:start
Would a believer in God

00:03:06.120 --> 00:03:08.455 position:35% line:83% align:start
ever read
such a scandalous scripture?

00:03:08.488 --> 00:03:11.458 position:19% line:83% align:start
Sir, just who are you?
How did you get in this place?

00:03:11.491 --> 00:03:14.162 position:10% line:83% align:start
Except for on Sundays, this
charnel house does not allow

00:03:14.194 --> 00:03:16.130 position:7% line:83% align:start
members of the general public
to enter.

00:03:16.164 --> 00:03:16.798 position:38% line:89% align:start
[thumps]

00:03:18.231 --> 00:03:20.034 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm aware of the restrictions,

00:03:20.068 --> 00:03:22.603 position:16% line:83% align:start
but I'm deathly allergic
to the sun.

00:03:22.637 --> 00:03:26.174 position:19% line:83% align:start
If I am not mistaken,
the sun sets at 6:19 today.

00:03:26.206 --> 00:03:28.275 position:19% line:83% align:start
Until that time comes,
I cannot go home,

00:03:28.308 --> 00:03:30.243 position:7% line:89% align:start
which is why I rested in here.

00:03:33.047 --> 00:03:34.515 position:35% line:89% align:start
Ah, I see.

00:03:34.549 --> 00:03:37.384 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, in that case, is there
anything I can do to help you?

00:03:37.819 --> 00:03:39.319 position:33% line:89% align:start
Not at all.

00:03:39.352 --> 00:03:41.189 position:10% line:83% align:start
-[young Father Pucchi] Okay.
-[approaching footsteps]

00:03:41.221 --> 00:03:42.322 position:19% line:83% align:start
[young Father Pucchi]
That's unfortunate.

00:03:43.958 --> 00:03:46.493 position:10% line:83% align:start
I won't tell the head priest
about encountering you,

00:03:46.527 --> 00:03:48.462 position:21% line:83% align:start
but you must be gone
when the sun sets.

00:03:50.464 --> 00:03:52.066 position:21% line:89% align:start
[young Dio chuckles]

00:03:52.100 --> 00:03:54.367 position:38% line:83% align:start
My, my.
You're an interesting one.

00:03:56.604 --> 00:03:57.304 position:38% line:89% align:start
How so?

00:03:57.337 --> 00:03:59.173 position:27% line:83% align:start
You're not going
to throw me out?

00:03:59.207 --> 00:04:00.808 position:16% line:89% align:start
What if I were a burglar

00:04:00.842 --> 00:04:04.045 position:5% line:83% align:start
who came here to rob this place
of its most valuable artwork,

00:04:04.078 --> 00:04:06.214 position:19% line:89% align:start
or worse, to kill you?

00:04:06.246 --> 00:04:08.348 position:33% line:83% align:start
Or perhaps,
you're just saying I can stay,

00:04:08.381 --> 00:04:11.485 position:19% line:83% align:start
but you actually plan
to rat me out to the police.

00:04:11.519 --> 00:04:12.987 position:19% line:83% align:start
[young Father Pucchi]
Is that what you want me to do?

00:04:14.387 --> 00:04:16.557 position:10% line:83% align:start
Though a thief wouldn't lie
about a sun allergy.

00:04:16.591 --> 00:04:18.526 position:13% line:89% align:start
It doesn't seem plausible.

00:04:18.559 --> 00:04:21.696 position:24% line:83% align:start
Not even the devil
would tell such a blatant lie.

00:04:21.729 --> 00:04:23.664 position:7% line:83% align:start
-[young Dio] Hold on a moment.
-[young Father Pucchi] Hm?

00:04:23.698 --> 00:04:26.333 position:13% line:83% align:start
[young Dio] Did you twist
your ankle because of me?

00:04:26.366 --> 00:04:27.400 position:24% line:89% align:start
Are you all right?

00:04:27.434 --> 00:04:28.970 position:24% line:89% align:start
No, it isn't that.

00:04:29.003 --> 00:04:31.404 position:10% line:89% align:start
Please don't worry about it.

00:04:31.438 --> 00:04:32.740 position:21% line:83% align:start
I've been like this
since my birth.

00:04:32.774 --> 00:04:35.576 position:16% line:83% align:start
They say I was born with
twisted toes on my left foot.

00:04:35.610 --> 00:04:38.411 position:13% line:83% align:start
However, it doesn't hinder
my ability to walk.

00:04:40.248 --> 00:04:41.582 position:30% line:89% align:start
[tense music]

00:04:41.616 --> 00:04:44.719 position:13% line:83% align:start
Do you believe in gravity
between individuals?

00:04:44.752 --> 00:04:47.155 position:7% line:83% align:start
You ended up tripping over me
of all people,

00:04:47.188 --> 00:04:48.723 position:27% line:83% align:start
but did you know
it was for a reason?

00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:52.093 position:19% line:89% align:start
W-What are you saying?

00:04:52.126 --> 00:04:53.628 position:27% line:89% align:start
[metal rattling]

00:04:53.661 --> 00:04:55.663 position:27% line:89% align:start
[rapid swishing]

00:04:55.997 --> 00:04:57.297 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:04:57.330 --> 00:04:59.066 position:24% line:83% align:start
-[metallic cling]
-Take this arrow.

00:04:59.100 --> 00:05:01.434 position:33% line:83% align:start
Consider it
a thank-you present.

00:05:01.468 --> 00:05:03.137 position:24% line:83% align:start
If you do not wish
to accept it,

00:05:03.171 --> 00:05:05.640 position:10% line:83% align:start
that is still perfectly fine
with me.

00:05:05.673 --> 00:05:09.677 position:10% line:83% align:start
But are not all meetings of
fate their own form of gravity?

00:05:09.710 --> 00:05:11.546 position:16% line:83% align:start
-We only did just meet.
-[young Father Pucchi shudders]

00:05:11.579 --> 00:05:14.615 position:21% line:83% align:start
So I don't know what
your first impression of me is,

00:05:14.649 --> 00:05:18.085 position:10% line:83% align:start
but I'm a traveler fueled by
the hope of fateful encounters.

00:05:18.119 --> 00:05:20.588 position:19% line:83% align:start
If ever you feel like
seeing me again someday...

00:05:20.621 --> 00:05:21.823 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:05:21.856 --> 00:05:25.358 position:7% line:83% align:start
[young Dio] ...aim that desire
towards the arrow and pray,

00:05:25.392 --> 00:05:27.995 position:16% line:83% align:start
no matter how many years
might have passed since now.

00:05:28.696 --> 00:05:29.831 position:38% line:89% align:start
Got it?

00:05:29.864 --> 00:05:32.465 position:21% line:83% align:start
All I ask is for you
to keep that in mind.

00:05:32.499 --> 00:05:34.202 position:7% line:89% align:start
[young Father Pucchi shudders]

00:05:34.235 --> 00:05:35.736 position:33% line:83% align:start
[young Dio]
Once we reach sundown,

00:05:35.770 --> 00:05:37.839 position:33% line:83% align:start
it shall be
like I was never here.

00:05:39.540 --> 00:05:41.441 position:21% line:89% align:start
[tense music builds]

00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:43.744 position:19% line:89% align:start
[breathing nervously]

00:05:47.414 --> 00:05:48.716 position:38% line:83% align:start
[gasps]
What's this?

00:05:49.817 --> 00:05:52.385 position:38% line:83% align:start
My toes,
the toes of my left foot!

00:05:52.954 --> 00:05:54.487 position:16% line:89% align:start
Th-They're not twisted!

00:05:55.323 --> 00:05:57.357 position:10% line:89% align:start
Hey, wait! Who even are you?

00:05:57.859 --> 00:05:58.626 position:30% line:89% align:start
[music fades]

00:06:00.862 --> 00:06:01.762 position:21% line:89% align:start
[church bells toll]

00:06:04.364 --> 00:06:05.933 position:19% line:83% align:start
-[footsteps approach]
-[woman] Please, Father.

00:06:06.934 --> 00:06:07.635 position:35% line:89% align:start
[exclaims]

00:06:07.668 --> 00:06:09.804 position:13% line:89% align:start
[woman] Listen to my plea.

00:06:09.837 --> 00:06:12.405 position:30% line:83% align:start
I beg of you,
I have a confession to make.

00:06:13.274 --> 00:06:14.642 position:27% line:89% align:start
Uh, yes. Well...

00:06:14.675 --> 00:06:16.143 position:33% line:83% align:start
One moment.
I'll get the priest...

00:06:16.177 --> 00:06:17.678 position:38% line:83% align:start
[woman]
I'm stricken with disease,

00:06:18.512 --> 00:06:20.715 position:10% line:89% align:start
and I fear I'm going to die.

00:06:20.748 --> 00:06:21.716 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:06:21.749 --> 00:06:24.552 position:16% line:83% align:start
[woman] There's no cure
that can help me now.

00:06:24.585 --> 00:06:28.155 position:19% line:83% align:start
But, my illness isn't
what I'm here to confess about.

00:06:29.891 --> 00:06:31.993 position:16% line:89% align:start
My sin was to my family.

00:06:33.426 --> 00:06:36.530 position:33% line:83% align:start
16 years ago
on the night of June 5th,

00:06:36.564 --> 00:06:39.466 position:13% line:83% align:start
after my newborn baby drew
his first and final breath,

00:06:39.499 --> 00:06:41.669 position:13% line:83% align:start
I traded him for another.
[sobs]

00:06:42.336 --> 00:06:43.738 position:13% line:89% align:start
While no one was looking,

00:06:43.771 --> 00:06:47.474 position:16% line:83% align:start
I took a stranger's baby
and left mine in his place.

00:06:48.009 --> 00:06:50.211 position:19% line:89% align:start
That baby was a twin.

00:06:50.244 --> 00:06:51.679 position:10% line:89% align:start
[young Father Pucchi gasps]

00:06:51.712 --> 00:06:53.514 position:13% line:83% align:start
[woman] When I think about
the baby's parents,

00:06:53.547 --> 00:06:54.849 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'm overcome with guilt!

00:06:55.316 --> 00:06:57.118 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whimpers]

00:06:57.151 --> 00:06:58.386 position:16% line:89% align:start
Though she wasn't mine,

00:06:58.451 --> 00:07:01.188 position:24% line:83% align:start
I raised the child
to the best of my ability.

00:07:02.123 --> 00:07:04.025 position:27% line:89% align:start
I was so happy.

00:07:04.058 --> 00:07:06.327 position:7% line:83% align:start
And this little boy I watched
go through life.

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:09.063 position:30% line:83% align:start
grew up to be
such a fine young man.

00:07:09.096 --> 00:07:13.034 position:13% line:83% align:start
However, if I die without
ever confessing... [sobs]

00:07:13.067 --> 00:07:15.236 position:24% line:83% align:start
What would happen
if I told him the truth

00:07:15.269 --> 00:07:17.571 position:33% line:83% align:start
that he has
a brother somewhere?

00:07:17.605 --> 00:07:19.674 position:10% line:83% align:start
Though, if he finally learns
what happened,

00:07:19.707 --> 00:07:22.209 position:27% line:83% align:start
that would mean
I've lost my son before I die!

00:07:22.843 --> 00:07:24.578 position:33% line:89% align:start
[whimpering]

00:07:24.979 --> 00:07:26.080 position:35% line:89% align:start
Are you...

00:07:26.113 --> 00:07:29.750 position:16% line:83% align:start
familiar at all with who
the family of the other son is?

00:07:29.784 --> 00:07:32.053 position:7% line:83% align:start
The other twin's family lived
in a big mansion

00:07:32.086 --> 00:07:33.453 position:19% line:89% align:start
in the next town over.

00:07:34.487 --> 00:07:36.791 position:41% line:83% align:start
Pucchi
is the family's last name.

00:07:38.526 --> 00:07:39.694 position:35% line:89% align:start
[clatters]

00:07:39.727 --> 00:07:41.128 position:7% line:89% align:start
I, like, really don't get it.

00:07:41.162 --> 00:07:43.798 position:5% line:83% align:start
What exactly do you see in that
juice delivery boy, anyway?

00:07:44.265 --> 00:07:45.232 position:38% line:89% align:start
I know.

00:07:45.266 --> 00:07:46.534 position:16% line:89% align:start
But that butt, though...

00:07:46.567 --> 00:07:48.069 position:21% line:83% align:start
-He's such a hottie.
-Just stop it already.

00:07:48.102 --> 00:07:50.438 position:19% line:83% align:start
I bet the loser comes
from a poor family.

00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.440 position:10% line:83% align:start
He probably doesn't even go
to high school.

00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:53.874 position:7% line:89% align:start
That's why he delivers juice.

00:07:54.742 --> 00:07:55.710 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:07:55.743 --> 00:07:58.045 position:33% line:83% align:start
Hey, Perla.
Doesn't that bag belong to you?

00:07:58.079 --> 00:07:59.013 position:13% line:89% align:start
Th-That guy just took it!

00:07:59.880 --> 00:08:01.315 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[exclaims]
-He's a purse-snatcher!

00:08:01.349 --> 00:08:02.984 position:16% line:89% align:start
Someone catch that guy!

00:08:03.017 --> 00:08:03.884 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whooshes]

00:08:04.652 --> 00:08:05.119 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[cracks]
-[exclaims]

