00:16:15.042 --> 00:16:18.011 position:7% line:89% align:start
What... What... What is this?

00:16:19.313 --> 00:16:22.049 position:5% line:83% align:start
The arrow that I'd been keeping
in my pocket?

00:16:22.082 --> 00:16:24.351 position:33% line:83% align:start
Once a life
has been taken away,

00:16:24.384 --> 00:16:26.921 position:24% line:83% align:start
it can never fully
be given back.

00:16:26.955 --> 00:16:29.356 position:24% line:83% align:start
But if your desire
is strong enough,

00:16:29.389 --> 00:16:31.458 position:24% line:83% align:start
and it's what you
truly wish for,

00:16:31.492 --> 00:16:34.896 position:19% line:83% align:start
you will be capable of
preserving her memory forever.

00:16:34.929 --> 00:16:37.799 position:19% line:83% align:start
The memory that lives
in her heart.

00:16:37.832 --> 00:16:40.334 position:21% line:83% align:start
This, my new friend,
is your awakening.

00:16:40.367 --> 00:16:41.001 position:38% line:89% align:start
[chokes]

00:16:41.034 --> 00:16:43.070 position:35% line:89% align:start
[splashes]

00:16:47.107 --> 00:16:49.511 position:27% line:89% align:start
[blood spatters]

00:16:49.544 --> 00:16:51.111 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[swooshes]
-Huh?

00:16:52.079 --> 00:16:54.047 position:10% line:89% align:start
Hey, who the hell is there?

00:16:54.081 --> 00:16:56.016 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're not that dumbass
who asked me

00:16:56.049 --> 00:16:57.919 position:16% line:83% align:start
to check if your wife's
been cheating, are ya?

00:16:57.952 --> 00:16:59.486 position:24% line:83% align:start
If you don't want
to get pumped with lead,

00:16:59.521 --> 00:17:01.088 position:24% line:83% align:start
I suggest you show
that ugly mug of yours--

00:17:02.557 --> 00:17:04.291 position:38% line:83% align:start
[gasps]
What the fuck?

00:17:04.324 --> 00:17:06.761 position:27% line:83% align:start
Hey, you're big
on information, yeah?

00:17:06.794 --> 00:17:08.061 position:35% line:83% align:start
[shudders]
Huh?

00:17:08.095 --> 00:17:10.364 position:10% line:83% align:start
[young Weather] If you know
so much, then tell me.

00:17:10.397 --> 00:17:12.199 position:27% line:83% align:start
Why the hell is
an infestation of snails

00:17:12.232 --> 00:17:13.701 position:16% line:89% align:start
coming out of your arm?

00:17:13.735 --> 00:17:16.504 position:13% line:83% align:start
Where do all these snails
keep coming from?

00:17:16.538 --> 00:17:19.172 position:16% line:83% align:start
Why is it only happening
around me?

00:17:19.206 --> 00:17:21.643 position:24% line:83% align:start
Okay, who the fuck
are you, guy?

00:17:21.676 --> 00:17:22.610 position:5% line:89% align:start
[young Weather] Is it true that

00:17:22.644 --> 00:17:24.311 position:21% line:83% align:start
Perla's brother was
the one who hired you?

00:17:24.344 --> 00:17:25.780 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Don't lie to me.
-No.

00:17:25.813 --> 00:17:27.916 position:7% line:89% align:start
That can't be. How are you...

00:17:27.949 --> 00:17:29.784 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[gunshot]
-[blood spatters]

00:17:29.817 --> 00:17:31.418 position:24% line:89% align:start
[snails sloshing]

00:17:31.451 --> 00:17:33.755 position:13% line:83% align:start
[young Weather] What's up
with all these snails?

00:17:33.788 --> 00:17:35.055 position:7% line:89% align:start
Why does this keep happening?

00:17:37.124 --> 00:17:38.492 position:33% line:89% align:start
[cocks gun]

00:17:38.526 --> 00:17:39.727 position:24% line:89% align:start
[trigger clicking]

00:17:40.394 --> 00:17:43.430 position:10% line:89% align:start
Dammit. I really can't die.

00:17:43.463 --> 00:17:44.231 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sputters]

00:17:45.800 --> 00:17:47.502 position:5% line:89% align:start
Only when I try to use the gun,

00:17:47.535 --> 00:17:49.704 position:21% line:83% align:start
the chamber's filled
with water.

00:17:50.738 --> 00:17:52.574 position:5% line:89% align:start
Why is it that I'm still alive?

00:17:52.607 --> 00:17:53.708 position:33% line:89% align:start
[gun clanks]

00:17:53.741 --> 00:17:56.578 position:7% line:83% align:start
[narrator] Weather was filled
with an immense rage,

00:17:56.611 --> 00:17:57.679 position:16% line:89% align:start
he was mad at the world

00:17:57.712 --> 00:18:00.748 position:16% line:83% align:start
for having to deal with
everything around him.

00:18:00.782 --> 00:18:03.250 position:7% line:89% align:start
Angry that he was still alive,

00:18:03.283 --> 00:18:04.719 position:19% line:89% align:start
and furious at himself

00:18:04.752 --> 00:18:07.254 position:33% line:83% align:start
for feeling
responsible for Perla's death.

00:18:08.488 --> 00:18:10.625 position:27% line:83% align:start
After realizing
what happened to her,

00:18:10.658 --> 00:18:13.995 position:10% line:83% align:start
Weather jumped off the cliff
trying to follow her lead,

00:18:14.028 --> 00:18:17.097 position:13% line:83% align:start
but a sudden gust of wind
blew him back up.

00:18:18.733 --> 00:18:21.502 position:5% line:83% align:start
Then, he tried to drown himself
in the lake,

00:18:21.536 --> 00:18:25.105 position:5% line:83% align:start
but the strong waves would only
push him back onto the shore.

00:18:26.406 --> 00:18:29.677 position:7% line:83% align:start
[young Weather] Why? Why can't
I just die and be with Perla?

00:18:30.011 --> 00:18:31.144 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sobs]

00:18:31.178 --> 00:18:36.249 position:35% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:18:36.283 --> 00:18:37.384 position:13% line:89% align:start
[narrator] In his despair,

00:18:37.417 --> 00:18:39.988 position:27% line:83% align:start
his rage became
a devastating fury.

00:18:40.021 --> 00:18:43.091 position:10% line:83% align:start
His hatred started to extend
not only to the townspeople,

00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:44.726 position:10% line:89% align:start
but to humanity in general.

00:18:44.759 --> 00:18:45.627 position:33% line:89% align:start
[drum beats]

00:18:48.128 --> 00:18:49.363 position:21% line:89% align:start
On the fourth night,

00:18:49.396 --> 00:18:52.366 position:13% line:83% align:start
a major snail infestation
had invaded the town.

00:18:52.967 --> 00:18:54.636 position:19% line:89% align:start
But why was it snails?

00:18:54.669 --> 00:18:57.170 position:24% line:83% align:start
And where exactly
did they come from?

00:18:57.204 --> 00:19:00.140 position:13% line:83% align:start
No one was able to explain
this sudden occurrence.

00:19:01.274 --> 00:19:02.977 position:7% line:89% align:start
The only person who understood

00:19:03.011 --> 00:19:07.180 position:7% line:83% align:start
what was going on was Enrico,
who woke up in a hospital.

00:19:07.982 --> 00:19:10.718 position:7% line:89% align:start
It's Wes... No, it's Weather.

00:19:10.752 --> 00:19:12.285 position:19% line:89% align:start
My brother isn't dead.

00:19:12.319 --> 00:19:14.488 position:21% line:83% align:start
Since he and I share
the same blood,

00:19:14.522 --> 00:19:18.258 position:13% line:83% align:start
the awakening of my powers
must have awakened his own.

00:19:18.291 --> 00:19:20.862 position:13% line:83% align:start
Just like how I wished for
the preservation of memories,

00:19:20.895 --> 00:19:23.898 position:13% line:83% align:start
this must be what Weather
desired unconsciously.

00:19:23.931 --> 00:19:26.333 position:7% line:83% align:start
If these snails were to start
crawling up my arm

00:19:26.366 --> 00:19:27.702 position:10% line:89% align:start
in order to do away with me,

00:19:27.735 --> 00:19:29.904 position:13% line:83% align:start
I would have to finish off
my brother.

00:19:31.471 --> 00:19:34.008 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'm willing to do anything
from now on,

00:19:34.042 --> 00:19:37.111 position:24% line:83% align:start
even if that means
I have to kill.

00:19:37.145 --> 00:19:39.881 position:24% line:83% align:start
After I'm through
with taking care of Weather,

00:19:39.914 --> 00:19:41.883 position:16% line:89% align:start
I shall go see that man.

00:19:41.916 --> 00:19:44.585 position:13% line:89% align:start
The one who is named Dio.

00:19:44.619 --> 00:19:47.220 position:30% line:83% align:start
Why does fate
bring two people together?

00:19:47.254 --> 00:19:49.691 position:30% line:83% align:start
I am convinced
that he knows the answer.

00:19:50.390 --> 00:19:52.060 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's what I want to learn.

00:19:52.093 --> 00:19:53.728 position:10% line:83% align:start
The answer to that question
is indeed

00:19:53.761 --> 00:19:56.329 position:21% line:83% align:start
the strongest power
this world may ever know

00:19:56.363 --> 00:19:58.265 position:16% line:89% align:start
and the ultimate truth.

00:19:58.298 --> 00:20:00.333 position:27% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music]

00:20:02.469 --> 00:20:04.072 position:7% line:89% align:start
[young Weather] Are you happy?

00:20:04.105 --> 00:20:06.040 position:21% line:83% align:start
Your sister, Perla,
ended up dying

00:20:06.074 --> 00:20:08.241 position:35% line:83% align:start
because of
your fucking request.

00:20:08.275 --> 00:20:11.546 position:38% line:83% align:start
And now,
my fury isn't satisfied.

00:20:11.579 --> 00:20:13.681 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll make you pay
right here and now.

00:20:14.148 --> 00:20:15.550 position:30% line:89% align:start
You're wrong.

00:20:15.583 --> 00:20:18.186 position:19% line:83% align:start
I put this into motion
because I am your brother.

00:20:18.218 --> 00:20:19.654 position:19% line:89% align:start
[young Weather gasps]

00:20:19.687 --> 00:20:21.723 position:21% line:83% align:start
But that connection
ends here today!

00:20:21.756 --> 00:20:25.126 position:24% line:83% align:start
Weather, I'm going
to eliminate you!

00:20:25.159 --> 00:20:25.960 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gurgling]

00:20:25.993 --> 00:20:27.028 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:20:27.061 --> 00:20:27.995 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whooshes]

00:20:31.566 --> 00:20:32.667 position:19% line:83% align:start
[young Father Pucchi]
Oh, Weather.

00:20:32.700 --> 00:20:34.468 position:30% line:83% align:start
You're merely
a hindrance to me.

00:20:35.069 --> 00:20:36.771 position:19% line:89% align:start
So I shall banish you

00:20:36.804 --> 00:20:38.873 position:16% line:89% align:start
along with the rainbow.

00:20:38.906 --> 00:20:43.044 position:19% line:83% align:start
Like Perla, every one
of your memories will vanish.

00:20:43.077 --> 00:20:47.148 position:7% line:83% align:start
And those without any memories
left are as good as dead.

00:20:47.181 --> 00:20:50.885 position:7% line:83% align:start
You shall live out the rest of
your days like a caged animal.

00:20:53.721 --> 00:20:55.123 position:27% line:89% align:start
[cage shutters]

00:20:55.156 --> 00:20:57.225 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music builds]

00:20:57.257 --> 00:21:00.862 position:7% line:89% align:start
[man] Prisoner number MA152403

00:21:00.895 --> 00:21:01.996 position:21% line:89% align:start
has been locked up!

00:21:05.066 --> 00:21:07.602 position:30% line:83% align:start
My only reason
for continuing to live

00:21:07.635 --> 00:21:10.838 position:5% line:83% align:start
is to settle the score with him
once and for all!

00:21:10.872 --> 00:21:13.975 position:21% line:83% align:start
What are you saying?
They've come back to you?

00:21:14.008 --> 00:21:15.342 position:27% line:83% align:start
You can remember
everything now?

00:21:16.043 --> 00:21:17.545 position:10% line:89% align:start
Then what are we doing here?

00:21:17.578 --> 00:21:20.413 position:16% line:83% align:start
Shouldn't we be heading
to where Jolyne is right now?

00:21:20.447 --> 00:21:22.315 position:33% line:83% align:start
I only came
with you for Jolyne.

00:21:22.349 --> 00:21:24.252 position:21% line:83% align:start
I don't give a damn
about your past!

00:21:24.284 --> 00:21:26.621 position:24% line:83% align:start
You don't wanna go
where Jolyne is currently.

00:21:26.654 --> 00:21:28.256 position:13% line:89% align:start
It would just be useless.

00:21:28.288 --> 00:21:29.422 position:33% line:89% align:start
And anyway,

00:21:29.456 --> 00:21:32.160 position:19% line:83% align:start
I need you by my side
so you can kill me.

00:21:32.193 --> 00:21:32.894 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia gasps]

00:21:33.561 --> 00:21:35.029 position:13% line:89% align:start
You have to take my life.

00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:37.932 position:19% line:89% align:start
Anastasia, I beg you.

00:21:37.965 --> 00:21:39.567 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:21:39.600 --> 00:21:41.401 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Ermes] And it's because of
this gruesome method of eating

00:21:41.434 --> 00:21:44.238 position:13% line:83% align:start
that these bugs are known
as snail suckers!

00:21:44.272 --> 00:21:45.840 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[grunts]
-Oraa, oraa, oraa, oraa, oraa!

00:21:45.873 --> 00:21:46.874 position:35% line:89% align:start
[shrieks]

00:21:48.276 --> 00:21:49.710 position:30% line:89% align:start
[both scream]

00:21:49.744 --> 00:21:50.878 position:24% line:89% align:start
Everyone, get in!

00:21:50.912 --> 00:21:51.444 position:30% line:89% align:start
[metal clanks]

00:21:52.680 --> 00:21:54.916 position:13% line:83% align:start
These suckers are crawling
in through the cracks!

00:21:54.949 --> 00:21:56.551 position:13% line:89% align:start
What should we do, Jolyne?

00:21:56.584 --> 00:21:59.620 position:5% line:83% align:start
It doesn't matter if they're in
or out of the car.

00:21:59.654 --> 00:22:03.257 position:10% line:83% align:start
Either way it goes, they're
gonna find us and start eating.

00:22:03.291 --> 00:22:04.391 position:13% line:89% align:start
So while they're snacking,

00:22:04.424 --> 00:22:06.393 position:13% line:89% align:start
we're going after Weather!

00:22:10.865 --> 00:22:13.400 position:24% line:83% align:start
["Distant Dreamer"
by Duffy playing]

